---
import AppShell from "../components/AppShell.astro";
import ScrollArrows from "../components/ScrollArrows.astro";
import type { AboutKind } from "../types";

interface Props {
  kinds: AboutKind[];
}

const { kinds } = Astro.props;
---

<AppShell activeNav="About" hideSelectedHud>
  <article class="tl-about-page">
    <header class="tl-about-hero">
      <h1>About.</h1>
      <p class="tl-about-lede">
        thinkinglabs is my public working surface: a markdown repository turned into a website,
        feed system, index, and agent-readable map of my work.
      </p>
    </header>

    <figure class="tl-about-portrait" aria-label="Portrait">
      <picture>
        <source
          srcset="/images/about-portrait-dark.jpg"
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
          type="image/jpeg"
        />
        <source
          srcset="/images/about-portrait-light.webp"
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)"
          type="image/webp"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/about-portrait-light.webp"
          alt="Tom smiling in warm side light."
          width="2048"
          height="2048"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </picture>
    </figure>

    <section class="tl-about-section tl-about-intro" aria-labelledby="about-what-title">
      <p class="tl-about-kicker">What this is</p>
      <div class="tl-about-copy">
        <h2 id="about-what-title">A desk left in public.</h2>
        <p>
          It is not a portfolio and not quite a blog. It holds rough thoughts, stricter claims,
          predictions, project notes, decisions, questions, and the outside inputs that changed
          the shape of the work.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work mostly on AI systems and the operational layer around them. The parts I care
          about tend to be the parts that make systems legible: what changed, why a decision was
          made, what evidence supports a claim, and what would make me change my mind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-about-section" aria-labelledby="about-system-title">
      <p class="tl-about-kicker">The system</p>
      <div class="tl-about-copy">
        <h2 id="about-system-title">The repository is the durable object.</h2>
        <p>
          The web UI, JSON feeds, SQLite index, MCP surfaces, and Markdown URL variants are
          derived views over the same source. {
            "Canonical public content pages, listings, and selected static pages"
          } have agent-readable Markdown siblings by appending
          <code>.md</code> to the slashless URL, with <code>/index.md</code> standing in for the
          homepage.
        </p>
        <p>
          That keeps the machine surface rigid without making the writing brittle: edit the
          files, rebuild the surfaces, and let the public version stay close to the working
          version.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-about-inventory" aria-labelledby="about-inventory-title">
      <div class="tl-about-inventory-head">
        <p class="tl-about-kicker">Structure</p>
        <h2 id="about-inventory-title">The public shape of the repository.</h2>
        <p>
          Each entry type has a job. Some are loose enough to catch a thought before it
          disappears; others are strict enough to make drift visible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tl-about-kind-grid" data-tl-about-kind-rail>
        {
          kinds.map((kind) => (
            <a
              class="tl-about-kind"
              href={kind.href}
              data-entity={kind.slug}
              aria-label={`${kind.name}: ${kind.gloss}`}
            >
              <span class="tl-about-kind-visual" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="tl-about-kind-meta">
                <span class="tl-about-kind-count">
                  {kind.count} {kind.count === 1 ? "entry" : "entries"}
                </span>
                <span class="tl-about-kind-title">{kind.name}</span>
                <span class="tl-about-kind-gloss">{kind.gloss}</span>
              </span>
            </a>
          ))
        }
      </div>
      <ScrollArrows
        target="[data-tl-about-kind-rail]"
        items=".tl-about-kind"
        label="Repository structure"
        variant="header"
        rowOnly
      />
    </section>

    <section class="tl-about-section" aria-labelledby="about-reading-title">
      <p class="tl-about-kicker">How to read it</p>
      <div class="tl-about-copy">
        <h2 id="about-reading-title">Incomplete is part of the contract.</h2>
        <p>
          A claim can be revised. A prediction can resolve badly. A project can go dormant. The
          useful thing is not that every object is polished, but that the system leaves enough
          structure behind to return later and inspect what happened.
        </p>
        <p>
          I want the tone of the site to stay calm because the work benefits from calm. There
          should be enough empty space to read a sentence, enough metadata to audit it, and not
          much more than that.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-about-section" aria-labelledby="about-work-title">
      <p class="tl-about-kicker">Work</p>
      <div class="tl-about-copy">
        <h2 id="about-work-title">AI systems, made legible.</h2>
        <p>
          I work for <a href="https://wild.as">wild.as</a>. Reach out at
          <a href="mailto:tom@wild.as">tom@wild.as</a> or
          <a href="mailto:tom@flaming.codes">tom@flaming.codes</a> for personal messages.
          I also own <a href="https://flaming.codes">flaming.codes</a>, my previous site.
        </p>
        <p>
          Wild works with new technologies in the pragmatic sense: putting new capabilities into
          production when they make software clearer, faster, or more useful. A large part of that
          work right now is agentic software engineering: using agents every day, building the
          harnesses around them, and learning where human judgment still has to stay close to the
          loop.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tl-about-colophon" aria-label="Colophon">
      <p class="tl-about-kicker">Colophon</p>
      <p>
        Built with Astro, markdown content collections, deterministic feeds, a derived SQLite
        index, and a small MCP server for agent access. The typography and navigation are meant to
        make the repository feel like a working surface rather than a publication schedule.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</AppShell>

<style>
  .tl-about-page {
    display: grid;
    gap: 9rem;
    width: min(100%, 74rem);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding: 10rem 24px 12rem;
    color: var(--tl-ink);
  }

  .tl-about-hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 58rem;
  }

  .tl-about-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--tl-muted);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 650;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tl-about-hero h1,
  .tl-about-copy h2,
  .tl-about-inventory-head h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-weight: 650;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-hero h1 {
    font-size: 84px;
    line-height: 0.94;
  }

  .tl-about-lede {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--tl-prose-ink);
    font-size: 30px;
    font-weight: 520;
    line-height: 1.22;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-portrait {
    width: min(100%, 64rem);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .tl-about-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(9rem, 0.36fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .tl-about-intro {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .tl-about-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 48rem;
  }

  .tl-about-copy h2,
  .tl-about-inventory-head h2 {
    max-width: 16ch;
    font-size: 44px;
    line-height: 1.02;
  }

  .tl-about-copy p,
  .tl-about-inventory-head p,
  .tl-about-colophon p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--tl-prose-ink);
    font-size: 19px;
    font-weight: 420;
    line-height: 1.72;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-copy code {
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-family: var(--tl-font);
    font-size: 0.94em;
    font-weight: 560;
  }

  .tl-about-copy a,
  .tl-about-kind,
  .tl-about-colophon a {
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .tl-about-copy a:hover,
  .tl-about-kind:hover {
    color: var(--tl-muted);
  }

  .tl-about-inventory {
    display: grid;
    gap: 4.5rem;
    width: 100vw;
    min-width: 0;
    margin-inline: calc((100% - 100vw) / 2);
  }

  .tl-about-inventory-head {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.75rem;
    width: min(74rem, calc(100vw - 48px));
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-grid {
    display: flex;
    align-items: start;
    gap: clamp(9rem, 13vw, 15rem);
    width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
    overflow-y: hidden;
    overscroll-behavior-x: contain;
    scroll-padding-inline: 0;
    scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    scrollbar-width: none;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-grid::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 0;
    height: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-kind {
    --card-aspect: 1 / 1;
    --card-width: 16rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);
    --tl-card-shadow: var(--tl-gallery-shadow);
    --tl-card-hover-shadow: var(--tl-gallery-hover-shadow);
    display: grid;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: clamp(var(--card-width), 18vw, calc(var(--card-width) + 9rem));
    gap: 1.15rem;
    align-content: start;
    scroll-snap-align: center;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+1) {
    --card-width: 16rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 3 / 4;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+2) {
    --card-width: 22rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(11rem, 9vw, 15.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 4 / 3;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+3) {
    --card-width: 16rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 3 / 4;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+4) {
    --card-width: 17.5rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8.75rem, 9vw, 13.25rem);
    --card-aspect: 1 / 1;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+5) {
    --card-width: 22rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(11rem, 9vw, 15.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 4 / 3;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+6) {
    --card-width: 16rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8rem, 9vw, 12.5rem);
    --card-aspect: 3 / 4;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:nth-child(7n+7) {
    --card-width: 17.5rem;
    --card-half-width: clamp(8.75rem, 9vw, 13.25rem);
    --card-aspect: 1 / 1;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:first-child {
    margin-inline-start: calc(50vw - var(--card-half-width));
  }

  .tl-about-kind:last-child {
    margin-inline-end: calc(50vw - var(--card-half-width));
  }

  .tl-about-kind-visual {
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    overflow: hidden;
    aspect-ratio: var(--card-aspect);
    background: var(--tl-entity-gradient-luster), var(--tl-entity-gradient, var(--tl-soft));
    background-blend-mode: var(--tl-entity-gradient-blend);
    box-shadow: var(--tl-card-shadow);
    transition: box-shadow 0.55s ease;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-visual::before {
    position: absolute;
    inset: -18%;
    background: var(--tl-entity-gradient-luster), var(--tl-entity-gradient, var(--tl-soft));
    background-blend-mode: var(--tl-entity-gradient-blend);
    content: "";
    transform: rotate(-4deg) scale(1.08);
    transform-origin: var(--tl-gradient-origin, 50% 50%);
    animation: tl-entity-tile-drift var(--tl-gradient-duration, 28s) ease-in-out infinite
      alternate;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:hover .tl-about-kind-visual,
  .tl-about-kind:focus-visible .tl-about-kind-visual {
    box-shadow: var(--tl-card-hover-shadow);
  }

  .tl-about-kind:focus-visible {
    outline: none;
  }

  .tl-about-kind:focus-visible .tl-about-kind-visual {
    outline: 2px solid var(--tl-focus);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-meta {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-count {
    color: var(--tl-subtle);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 620;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-title {
    color: var(--tl-ink);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 650;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .tl-about-kind-gloss {
    color: var(--tl-muted);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 420;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .tl-about-colophon {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .tl-about-colophon p:last-child {
    color: var(--tl-muted);
    font-size: 17px;
  }

  .tl-about-inventory :global(.tl-scroll-arrows) {
    justify-self: center;
    margin-top: -2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .tl-about-page {
      gap: 7rem;
      padding-top: 8rem;
    }

    .tl-about-hero h1 {
      font-size: 68px;
    }

    .tl-about-lede {
      font-size: 26px;
    }

    .tl-about-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .tl-about-kind-grid {
      gap: 6rem;
    }

    .tl-about-kind {
      width: min(72vw, var(--card-width-mobile, 18rem));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .tl-about-page {
      gap: 5.5rem;
      padding: 7rem 18px 8rem;
    }

    .tl-about-hero {
      gap: 1.6rem;
    }

    .tl-about-hero h1 {
      font-size: 52px;
    }

    .tl-about-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }

    .tl-about-copy h2,
    .tl-about-inventory-head h2 {
      font-size: 34px;
    }

    .tl-about-copy p,
    .tl-about-inventory-head p {
      font-size: 17px;
    }

    .tl-about-kind-grid {
      gap: 5rem;
    }

    .tl-about-kind {
      width: min(78vw, var(--card-width-mobile, 15rem));
    }

    .tl-about-kind:nth-child(3n+2) {
      --card-width-mobile: 20rem;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .tl-about-kind-visual::before {
      animation: none;
    }
  }
</style>
